events.description: The release of seasonally adjusted unemployment data for Ireland for the month of January 2026.

facts.fact_text: Ireland's seasonally adjusted unemployment rate was 4.7% in January 2026, unchanged from the revised December 2025 figure.

evidences.evidence_text: The seasonally adjusted unemployment rate stood at 4.7% in January 2026, unchanged from a downwardly revised figure in December 2025.

facts.fact_text: The number of unemployed individuals in Ireland increased by 600 month-on-month to a total of 138,400.

evidences.evidence_text: The number of unemployed persons increased by 600 month-on-month to 138,400.

facts.fact_text: The youth unemployment rate for those aged 15-24 rose to 11.8% in January 2026 from 11.4% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: the youth unemployment rate, rose to 11.8% from 11.4% in December

facts.fact_text: The unemployment rate for individuals aged 25-74 decreased to 3.6% from 3.7%.

evidences.evidence_text: whereas the rate for those aged 25–74 ticked lower to 3.6% from 3.7%.
